                <h1>DHL: A Journey Through Logistics History</h1>
                <p>DHL began in 1969 when Adrian Dalsey, Larry Hillblom, and Robert Lynn launched a door-to-door courier service in San Francisco. Initially focused on document delivery, DHL quickly expanded internationally, becoming a recognized global leader in logistics and express shipping. Acquired by Deutsche Post in 2002, DHL continues to innovate in the logistics sector.</p>
